  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">African Coffee Special Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Most small coffee farmers lack the knowledge of global markets to get the best price for their product and avoid exploitation. This project trains farmer&#x2019;s co-operatives across Africa to produce high quality coffee that demands a good price. It promotes sustainable farming practices that are resilient to climate change, and helps women to take an equal role in running the organisation. The project gives assistance with marketing, certification and business management so that co-operatives can thrive in the global marketplace, and the different co-operatives are encouraged to share their knowledge. As the farmers collectively own the co-operatives, the project helps them make a decent living and improve their lives.</narrative>
  </description>
